							<div class="mw-indicators">
		</div>

						<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
					</div>
					<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
					
					
					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Vair_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="Vair (disambiguation)">Vair (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Varied tincture or fur in heraldry</div>
<div class="side-box side-box-right plainlinks sistersitebox">
<div class="side-box-flex">
<div class="side-box-image"><span class="noviewer" typeof="mw:File"><span><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg/40px-Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg.png" decoding="async" width="40" height="40" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg/60px-Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg/80px-Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="512" data-file-height="512" /></span></span></div>
<div class="side-box-text plainlist">Look up <i><b><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/vair" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:vair"> vair</a></b></i> in Wiktionary, the free dictionary.</div></div>
</div>
<div style="float:right;clear:right"><figure typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Arms_of_Beauchamp_(of_Hatch).svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Arms_of_Beauchamp_%28of_Hatch%29.svg/200px-Arms_of_Beauchamp_%28of_Hatch%29.svg.png" decoding="async" width="200" height="240" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Arms_of_Beauchamp_%28of_Hatch%29.svg/300px-Arms_of_Beauchamp_%28of_Hatch%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Arms_of_Beauchamp_%28of_Hatch%29.svg/400px-Arms_of_Beauchamp_%28of_Hatch%29.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="450" data-file-height="541" /></a><figcaption>Heraldic vair, arms of <a href="/wiki/Baron_Beauchamp" title="Baron Beauchamp">Baron Beauchamp</a> and of <a href="/wiki/Hellemmes" class="mw-redirect" title="Hellemmes">Hellemmes</a> in <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">France</a></figcaption></figure></div>
<p><b>Vair</b> (<span class="rt-commentedText nowrap"><span class="IPA nopopups noexcerpt" lang="en-fonipa"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title="Help:IPA/English">/<span style="border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title="&#39;v&#39; in &#39;vie&#39;">v</span><span title="/ɛər/: &#39;are&#39; in &#39;bare&#39;">ɛər</span></span>/</a></span></span>; from <a href="/wiki/Latin" title="Latin">Latin</a> <i>varius</i> "variegated"), originating as a processed form of <a href="/wiki/Squirrel" title="Squirrel">squirrel</a> <a href="/wiki/Fur" title="Fur">fur</a>, gave its name to a set of different patterns used in <a href="/wiki/Heraldry" title="Heraldry">heraldry</a>. Heraldic vair represents a kind of fur common in the <a href="/wiki/Middle_Ages" title="Middle Ages">Middle Ages</a>, made from pieces of the greyish-blue backs of squirrels sewn together with pieces of the animals' white underbellies. Vair is the second-most common <a href="/wiki/Heraldic_fur" class="mw-redirect" title="Heraldic fur">fur in heraldry</a>, after <a href="/wiki/Ermine_(heraldry)" title="Ermine (heraldry)">ermine</a>.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (February 2022)">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>
</p>
<meta property="mw:PageProp/toc" />
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Origins">Origins</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Origins"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div style="float:right;clear:right"></div>
<p>The word <i>vair</i>, with its variant forms <i>veir</i> and <i>vairé</i>, was brought into <a href="/wiki/Middle_English" title="Middle English">Middle English</a> from <a href="/wiki/Old_French" title="Old French">Old French</a>, from <a href="/wiki/Latin" title="Latin">Latin</a> <i><span title="Latin-language text"><i lang="la">varius</i></span></i> "variegated",<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and has been alternatively termed <i><span title="Latin-language text"><i lang="la">variorum opus</i></span></i> (Latin, meaning "variegated work").<sup id="cite_ref-fur_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-fur-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The squirrel in question is a variety of the <a href="/wiki/Red_squirrel" title="Red squirrel">Eurasian red squirrel</a>, <i>Sciurus vulgaris</i>. In the coldest parts of Northern and Central Europe, especially the <a href="/wiki/Baltic_Sea" title="Baltic Sea">Baltic region</a>, the winter coat of this squirrel is blue-grey on the back and white on the belly, and was much used for the <a href="/wiki/Lining_(sewing)" title="Lining (sewing)">lining</a> of <a href="/wiki/Cloak" title="Cloak">cloaks</a> called <i>mantles</i>. It was sewn together in alternating cup-shaped pieces of back and belly fur, resulting in a pattern of grey-blue and grey-white which, when simplified in heraldic drawing and painting, became blue and white in alternating pieces.<sup id="cite_ref-fur_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-fur-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional center">
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:VairUnit_svg_element.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="A unit of the heraldic fur vair, pointing downwards"><img alt="A unit of the heraldic fur vair, pointing downwards" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/VairUnit_svg_element.svg/85px-VairUnit_svg_element.svg.png" decoding="async" width="85" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/VairUnit_svg_element.svg/127px-VairUnit_svg_element.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/VairUnit_svg_element.svg/170px-VairUnit_svg_element.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="744" data-file-height="1052" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">A unit of the heraldic fur <b>vair</b>, pointing downwards</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Russian_squirrel_belly_skins.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Vair fur"><img alt="Vair fur" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Russian_squirrel_belly_skins.jpg/79px-Russian_squirrel_belly_skins.jpg" decoding="async" width="79" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Russian_squirrel_belly_skins.jpg/119px-Russian_squirrel_belly_skins.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Russian_squirrel_belly_skins.jpg/158px-Russian_squirrel_belly_skins.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1166" data-file-height="1768" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Vair fur</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Coa_England_Family_Beauchamp_of_Hatch.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Vair ancien"><img alt="Vair ancien" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Coa_England_Family_Beauchamp_of_Hatch.svg/104px-Coa_England_Family_Beauchamp_of_Hatch.svg.png" decoding="async" width="104" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Coa_England_Family_Beauchamp_of_Hatch.svg/156px-Coa_England_Family_Beauchamp_of_Hatch.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Coa_England_Family_Beauchamp_of_Hatch.svg/208px-Coa_England_Family_Beauchamp_of_Hatch.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="260" data-file-height="300" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Vair ancien</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Blason_Coucy-le-Chateau.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Barry of six vair and gules, arms of the Lords of Coucy"><img alt="Barry of six vair and gules, arms of the Lords of Coucy" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Blason_Coucy-le-Chateau.svg/109px-Blason_Coucy-le-Chateau.svg.png" decoding="async" width="109" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Blason_Coucy-le-Chateau.svg/164px-Blason_Coucy-le-Chateau.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Blason_Coucy-le-Chateau.svg/218px-Blason_Coucy-le-Chateau.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="660" /></a></span></div>
